learning_outcomes.en:
Student passing through the course:
* Knows and understands the main microscopy and physical analysis methods. Uses correctly (orally and in writing) the main terms of microscopy and physical analysis methods in both English and Estonian languages.
* Has base knowledge of the vacuum techniques used;
* Knows and understands the working principles of optical, scanning and transmission electron microscopes and scanning probe microscopes, electron and X-ray fluorescence- and electron spectrometers and X-ray microanalyzers, secondary ion mass-spectrometers, and knows their applications, where and for what this type of analyzing equipment are used;
* Obtains the first practical experiences for solid samples characterization with reflective optical-, scanning electron and atomic force microscopes, and X-ray fluorescence spectrometers, and with the preparation of the samples.
